  <li>Stir together flour, baking powder, sugar, and salt in medium size bowl.</li>
  <li>Cut in butter until crumbly</li>
  <li>Stir in milk to make a soft dough.</li>
  <li>Drop by spoonfuls into boiling stew. Cover and simmer 15 minutes without lifting lid.</li>
  <li>Serve.</li>
  <li>(Optional) To make parsley dumplings, add 1 tablespoon parsley flakes to the dry ingredients.</li>
